**Abstract:**
Essay fragment dated May 14, 1996 titled "Depth" analyzing Merleau-Ponty's Phenomenology of Perception on spatial experience. Opens with Merleau-Ponty quotation on depth as "the most existential of all dimensions." Argues that while Merleau-Ponty offers an alternative to Intellectualism and Empiricism, his analysis remains partially influenced by the visual paradigm he criticizes.

